Title: Exercise and sport science
Description: Our exercise and sport science program is professionally accredited by Exercise and Sports Science Australia and explores the physical health, wellbeing and performance of elite athletes, individuals and teams through training, coaching, research and more. Deakin is the #1 ranked sport science school in Australia, and our course will put you on the path to becoming an elite sport scientist, ready to work with individual athletes and sporting teams (ShanghaiRanking's Global Ranking of Sport Science Schools and Departments 2018).

Title: Medical imaging
Description: Our medical imaging course offers the perfect mix of knowledge and clinical experience needed to launch your career as a registered diagnostic radiographer, with training in techniques like ultrasound, magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) and CT. Develop clinical skills under the supervision of experienced practitioners in a range of settings and graduate with the knowledge and skills to work as a highly competent and in demand professionals.

Title: Medicine
Description: Our Doctor of Medicine places a strong emphasis on clinical skills development, teamwork and communication training, providing the best opportunities for medical training in metropolitan, regional and rural settings. Learn through problem-based seminars and practical classes before undergoing intensive clinical training within professional health services across Victoria.

Title: Health sciences
Description: Get ready to tackle the biggest issues in health right now with our health sciences program. With 12 unique majors you can tailor your learning to align with your interests and passions - then choose up to three majors to diversify your learning and boost your employability. Our Bachelor of Health Sciences ensures you graduate ready to make a difference to the lives of others across health fields including community, population and government.

Title: Deakin's Elite Athlete Program
Description: Learn about Deakin's Elite Athlete Program and how Deakin can assist you with balancing your studies and sporting commitments. Hear from current students about how they utilise our program to help them succeed both on and off the field.

Title: Optometry
Description: Our 3.5-year accelerated optometry course is a specialised combined degree that focuses on detecting, managing and treating eye and vision disorders and supplying corrective solutions. You will learn about visual health issues and their impact on communities around the world. Our course leads to registration as an optometrist and provides graduates with the discipline-specific knowledge required to practise as an optometrist throughout Australia and New Zealand.

You will learn about visual health issues and their impact on communities around the world. Our course leads to registration as an optometrist and provides graduates with the discipline-specific knowledge required to practise as an optometrist throughout Australia and New Zealand.

Title: Science
Description: Not just about laboratory work - science prepares you for a range of real-life settings that science graduates work in. Choose a general or specialist degree, study abroad or combine science with commerce, teaching, law or arts.
Location: Bldg ia, Room ia1.006, Peter Thwaites Lecture Theatre

Title: Forensic science
Description: Study our professionally accredited forensic science degree and ensure you're equipped with the formal training to examine and present scientific evidence. Upon graduation you'll be ready to work in fields including pharmaceutical and chemical industries, risk analysis, insurance investigation or as a forensic scientist.
Location: Bldg ia, Room ia1.006, Peter Thwaites Lecture Theatre

Title: Biomedical science
Description: Discover how a degree in biomedical science can lead to a range of careers. Learn how you could find yourself in fields including biomedical research, genetic counselling, patent law, genetic engineering, hospital and laboratory science, veterinary science, and pharmaceutical/medical sales - or, use this degree as a pathway to further studies in medicine.
Location: Bldg ia, Room ia1.006, Peter Thwaites Lecture Theatre

Title: Criminology
Description: Criminology looks different in every field - come and learn how criminology looks in areas including policing, policy development, correctional services, intelligence, crime prevention and security services.
Location: Bldg ia, Room ia1.006, Peter Thwaites Lecture Theatre

Title: Psychology
Description: Discover how our psychology courses expose you to the biological, developmental, social and cognitive factors that affect the way humans think, feel and behave. Start on the path to becoming a registered psychologist equipped to work in a range of psychology fields such as clinical, forensic, organisational, educational, health and more. Undergraduate psychology at Deakin leads the way among Victorian universities and is ranked by our students to be well above the national benchmark for education experience, learning resources and teaching quality (Quality Indicators for Learning and Teaching (QILT) 2018).
Location: Bldg ia, Room ia1.006, Peter Thwaites Lecture Theatre

Title: Criminology
Description: Criminology looks different in every field - come and learn how criminology looks in areas including policing, policy development, correctional services, intelligence, crime prevention and security services.
Location: Bldg ia, Room ia1.006, Peter Thwaites Lecture Theatre

Title: Deakin Live broadcast
Description: Deakin Live provides students the opportunity to broadcast live sporting events across Melbourne and is the first of its kind as a crew of university students broadcast national-level competitions across Melbourne. Come and see a real-world example of our communication and creative arts students at work during their Deakin Live internship via video displays and interviews.

Title: Writing and literature hub - The Poescope
Description: Do you secretly consult the horoscope page in the newspaper, or have a permanent bookmark for astrological advice in your phone? Look no further than poescope. Our trained clairvoyants will offer you cryptic and vague advice that you can interpret in any way that suits you.

Title: Pathways to Deakin
Description: The traditional path from Year 12 to university isn't the only way to Deakin. Learn more about our alternate pathways to starting your dream degree at Deakin, either through courses at Deakin, with our partner Deakin College or our TAFE partners across Victoria.

Title: Pathway to Deakin - Deakin College
Description: Diploma courses include business, commerce, communication, construction management, design, engineering, film, television and animation, health sciences, information technology and science - all pathways into second year at Deakin.

Title: Writing and literature
Description: Hear about our courses in writing and literature and find out how you can be a part of Geelong's very own literary and creative writing group.

Title: Life at Deakin
Description: Thinking about studying at Deakin but not sure what to expect? Take a walk through our student experience from your offer to your first exam and find out what a typical day might look like for you.
Pre_selected: Bachelor of Information Technology; Bachelor of Cyber Security

Title: Study online at our Cloud Campus
Description: When you study online with the Cloud Campus, you are supported by outstanding digital resources and tools as well as having access to the full range of learning and support services offered by the University. Take classes, submit assessments and participate in discussions all via the cloud.

Title: Deakin Accelerate - VCE extension studies
Description: Complete two units of a first-year university subject during Year 12, either on campus or online through Deakin Accelerate. Find out more about the benefits of our program and how it will help you get a head start on your university studies.

Title: Returning to study as mature-age and non-Year 12 students
Description: Looking to return to study? This session provides a guide on choosing the right course for you and tips on how to navigate the application process. Learn how study can suit your lifestyle, with flexible delivery options to help juggle work and your life commitments.

Title: Communications - journalism, public relations and digital media
Description: Find out how journalism, public relations and digital media will equip you with the knowledge and skills you need for an exciting career in communications.

Title: Deakin residences accommodation
Description: Join us to tour and learn more about the variety of accommodation options available at our Waurn Ponds campus. Discover the great benefits of living so close to campus, exclusive programs and events for residents and what it's like to be part of an enthusiastic and supporting community, all while making friends for life.

Title: Global experiences with Deakin Abroad
Description: Study overseas and gain credit towards your degree, without extending your time at Deakin. Experience new cultures, become a global citizen and gain that competitive edge.

Title: Communications - journalism, public relations and digital media
Description: Find out how journalism, public relations and digital media will equip you with the knowledge and skills you need for an exciting career in communications.

Title: Deakin residences accommodation
Description: Join us to tour and learn more about the variety of accommodation options available at our Waurn Ponds campus. Discover the great benefits of living so close to campus, exclusive programs and events for residents and what it's like to be part of an enthusiastic and supporting community, all while making friends for life.
Pre_selected: Bachelor of Information Technology; Bachelor of Cyber Security; Bachelor of Arts

Title: Journalism student showcase
Description: Come and visit the media hub. Learn how our journalism students create the stories you see on DScribe, our journalism student online news portal.

Title: Early years education
Description: Did you know our four-year early years education course is really a dual qualification? Find out how you can become qualified to teach in early childhood, as well as primary settings.

Title: Master of Teaching
Description: Looking for a career change? The Master of Teaching enables graduates from various disciplines to gain teaching qualifications in one of early childhood, primary or secondary education strands, or dual qualifications in primary/early childhood or primary/secondary.
Location: Bldg ib, Rooms ib4.205 and ib4.206

Title: Master of Applied Learning and Teaching (secondary teaching)
Description: Looking for a career change? Join us to learn how our postgraduate initial teacher qualification equips you with the knowledge, skills and experience to use applied learning methods for learning and teaching in youth education settings and vocational education.
Location: Bldg ib, Rooms ib4.205 and ib4.206

Title: Associate Degree of Education
Description: Our Associate Degree of Education introduces you to university study and provides guaranteed entry into our Bachelor of Education (Primary) degree, with credit.
Location: Bldg ib, Rooms ib4.205 and ib4.206

Title: Associate Degree of Arts
Description: Our Associate Degree of Arts provides a pathway to university study and guaranteed entry into Deakin's Bachelor of Arts or Bachelor of Criminology. You also have the option to transition into other Deakin undergraduate programs, with credit.
Location: Bldg ib, Rooms ib4.205 and ib4.206

Title: Deakin teachers are classroom ready
Description: Spending time on placement is an integral part of our initial teacher education courses (early childhood, primary and secondary). Hear from students about their experiences and speak to members of our professional experience team.
Location: Bldg ib, Rooms ib4.205 and ib4.206

Title: Building employability skills for the jobs of the future
Description: Learn about how Deakin collaborates with employers to prepare graduates for the jobs and skills of the future. Learn about our programs that enhance graduate employability, including work-integrated learning, international experiences and DeakinTALENT - voted the most popular careers service by the Australian Graduate Recruitment Industry Association. Have the opportunity to speak with staff and students about programs and services that enhance employability skills.
Pre_selected: Bachelor of Health Sciences; Bachelor of Cyber Security

Title: Visit the library
Description: Explore our library by taking a look around, or join a casual tour upon request. Discover what makes our students love the library and learn about the spaces, facilities and services available.
Pre_selected: Bachelor of Information Technology; Bachelor of Health Sciences; Bachelor of Cyber Security; Bachelor of Arts

Title: Maggot racing
Description: How fast can a maggot go? Learn how maggots are being used to research the relationship between blowflies, maggots and bacteria, while watching them race each other.

Title: Bringing physiology to life through body paint
Description: What do our hands look like under the skin? Have your hands painted to find out and learn fun facts about the human body from our science students.

Title: Science laboratories
Description: Visit our science laboratories to see the sophisticated equipment used in teaching and research. Talk with current students and technical staff, and also perform some fundamental chemistry experiments.

Title: A day of ice and fire
Description: Watch as our scientists demonstrate some fundamental chemistry concepts in a fun and engaging way. Demonstrations conducted on the hour from 10am.

Title: Zoology, reptile and amphibian display
Description: Handle a range of native snakes, lizards and amphibians in a showcase of Australian wildlife - a petting zoo with a difference. Learn about the ecology and adaption of animals to Australia's unique environment.

Title: Zoology and animal science
Description: Study animal diversity, ecology and behaviour, comparative physiology, biochemistry, genetics, evolutionary biology and animal nutrition, with hands-on experience using native Australian fauna and ecosystems. Study zoology and animal science at Deakin and explore animal diversity, ecology and behaviour, comparative physiology, biochemistry, genetics, evolutionary biology and animal nutrition. Immerse yourself in the field with hands-on experience using native Australia fauna and ecosystems.

Title: Primary teaching
Description: Discover the rewards of studying a primary teaching degree. Hear from our friendly staff and learn more about selection, course information and career options.

Title: Marine science
Description: Our new Bachelor of Marine Science will give students the practical and theoretical knowledge required to work in the field of marine science. Discover how you'll gain extensive experience at the Queenscliff Marine Research Centre and develop an understanding of marine biology, ecology, oceanography and fisheries and aquaculture required to assess the environment as a marine scientist to ensure the sustainable of the world's oceans.

Title: Secondary teaching in health and physical education
Description: Become a health and physical education secondary school teacher - a career choice that promotes being physically active and healthy. Find out more on selection, course options, transition support and other career possibilities.

Title: Wildlife conservation and environmental sustainability
Description: Discover what it's like to study environmental management and wildlife conservation at Deakin. While environmental management focuses on finding sustainable solutions to the world's most pressing environmental problems, wildlife and conservation biology offers theoretical and practical experience in areas including wildlife ecology and biodiversity and conservation.

Title: Forensic science
Description: Study our professionally accredited forensic science degree and ensure you're equipped with the formal training to examine and present scientific evidence. Upon graduation you'll be ready to work in fields including pharmaceutical and chemical industries, risk analysis, insurance investigation or as a forensic scientist.

Title: Secondary teaching in the arts, sciences and maths
Description: Find out about the different pathways you can take towards your career as a secondary teacher. Specialise in fields including english, humanities, languages and social sciences, biology, chemistry, geography, environmental science and mathematics. Learn about selection, course information and career options.

Title: Primary teaching
Description: Discover the rewards of studying a primary teaching degree. Hear from our friendly staff and learn more about selection, course information and career options.

Title: Discover Deakin
Description: Find out all about the study options, exciting opportunities and experiences awaiting you at Deakin. Learn how our students are prepared for future career opportunities, and get tips on how to make the most of your Open Day visit.
Pre_selected: Bachelor of Health Sciences; Bachelor of Arts

Title: Nutrition science and dietetics
Description: Our nutrition course explores the vital role of food and nutrition in human health and disease prevention. You'll be equipped to pursue a pathway into dietetics or work as a nutritional specialist in a range of sectors including the food industry, media and marketing, nutrition research and education, public health and population nutrition, and self-employment and consulting.

Title: Money matters
Description: Learn everything you need to know about tuition fees, invoicing and HECS-HELP. Discover if you are eligible for a scholarship and how to apply.

Title: Understanding VTAC's SEAS
Description: Find out all you need to know about VTAC's Special Entry and Access Scheme (SEAS) from our specialists, including the application process, different SEAS categories and how SEAS impacts university selection.

Title: Discover Deakin
Description: Find out all about the study options, exciting opportunities and experiences awaiting you at Deakin. Learn how our students are prepared for future career opportunities, and get tips on how to make the most of your Open Day visit.

Title: IT showcase
Description: Visit our interactive IT display - explore new perspectives with analytics, smart technologies and virtual reality, meet our fun and cute humanoids and discover how IT is a part of everyday life. See some of our student work and exciting research.
Pre_selected: Bachelor of Information Technology; Bachelor of Cyber Security

Title: Information technology - cyber security, cloud computing, VR and creative technologies
Description: IT professionals are accelerating digital transformation across industry sectors, driving innovation and enabling economic growth. Learn how Deakin's Bachelor of Information Technology provides you with contemporary knowledge, skills and experience required for a successful career as an IT professional and explore the options available to tailor course outcomes to your career aspirations. This session will also explore the majors of study aligned with the bachelor of IT, allowing students to tailor their course offering.

Title: Cyber security
Description: Learn about the exciting field of cyber security, one of the newest and fastest growing areas of information technology. In this talk we'll cover what skills you need to be successful in this field and how Deakin's unique course can prepare you for a fast paced career in cyber security.
Pre_selected: Bachelor of Information Technology; Bachelor of Cyber Security

Title: IT alumni, student and research panel
Description: Hear from a panel comprising of Deakin IT alumni, current students and young researchers as they share their journeys through higher education and their tips on surviving and thriving at university and beyond.

Title: IT industry panel
Description: Learn about the state of the global IT industry, career opportunities and how studying IT at Deakin will prepare you with the skills in demand from industry professionals and leaders.

Title: Parents and caregivers guide to university
Description: Find out how to support your child transitioning from high school to University. Learn about the application process, selection and offers, support services for students and alternative pathways to study.

Title: Public health and health promotion
Description: Our public health and health promotion course gives you the skills to tackle big-picture population health problems and improve the health and wellbeing of individuals and communities around the world. Develop invaluable skills in program planning and evaluation, health education, community engagement and policy development and analysis. During the course, you can gain practical work experience in a health-related agency, ensuring you're job ready by the time you graduate.

Title: Institute of Koorie Education
Description: Discover how the Institute of Koorie Education (IKE) enables Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Australians the flexibility to gain access to higher education while still being able to maintain family and community obligations.
Location: Bldg kc, Institute of Koorie Education

Title: Environmental and civil engineering experience
Description: Come and learn about our environmental and civil engineering programs. Talk to our staff about studying environmental and civil engineering, what these courses involve, and future career options for graduates. Take the opportunity to visit our cutting edge facilities, including our three teaching laboratories dedicated to geomechanics (soil), structures and hydraulics/hydrology (water).

Title: International studies and work-integrated learning
Description: International Studies is a unique course combining study, workplace skills development, travel and real-world experience. Learn about the course structure, available majors and international experience options. Hear Deakin students talk about their experiences on study exchange, internships and study tours.
Location: Bldg kc, Institute of Koorie Education, Room kc2.203

Interest_area: Humanities, social sciences and languages; Media, communication and creative arts
Title: Arts
Description: Open up a world of career options by studying a Bachelor of Arts at Deakin. Learn how you can combine your interests and passions with our work integrated learning opportunities to prepare for your dream career.
Location: Bldg kc, Institute of Koorie Education, Room kc2.203

Title: Politics and policy studies, international relations, Middle East studies
Description: Find out about studying the exciting international politics and Middle East studies programs and the numerous employment opportunities for graduates.
Location: Bldg kc, Institute of Koorie Education, Room kc2.203

Title: Philosophy and religious studies
Description: Philosophy for life, from world religions to Freud, ethics to political philosophy, Deakin's philosophy program challenges your thinking. Study religion and philosophy, myth and ritual, religion and popular culture, Buddhist studies, Islamic studies and more.
Location: Bldg kc, Institute of Koorie Education, Room kc2.203

Title: Languages - Arabic, Chinese, Indonesian and Spanish
Description: Discover career-enhancing opportunities to engage internationally and study overseas. Consider where learning a language can take you.
Location: Bldg kc, Institute of Koorie Education, Room kc2.203

Title: History
Description: The insistence of the past in the present - history at Deakin. Join this information session to explore our stimulating and challenging history program.
Location: Bldg kc, Institute of Koorie Education, Room kc2.203

Title: Geography and society
Description: An understanding of everything from how and why volcanos are formed to the impact of overcrowding in urban areas, geographers are integral to finding solutions to some of the biggest issues in the world. Find out more about studying geography at Deakin.
Location: Bldg kc, Institute of Koorie Education, Room kc2.203

Title: Sociology and anthropology
Description: Learn to change the way you see the world through the study of sociology and anthropology. Study the people around you - the rich, poor, strong, weak, powerful, oppressed and all in between. Delve into the lives of people in different societies and learn how relevant these studies can be to your career.
Location: Bldg kc, Institute of Koorie Education, Room kc2.203

Interest_area: Humanities, social sciences and languages; Media, communication and creative arts
Title: Gender and sexuality studies
Description: Discover Deakin's major in gender and sexuality studies. Learn about the significance of sex, gender and sexuality in contemporary and historical cultures.
Location: Bldg kc, Institute of Koorie Education, Room kc2.203

Title: Engineering experience
Description: Visit our engineering labs, witness the power of the high voltage lab and immerse yourself in a virtual world, all the while experiencing all that 21st century engineering education has to offer. Our CADET facility showcases labs including virtual reality, high voltage, product prototype and product realisation, material, electrical engineering, renewable energy, mechatronics and physics.

Title: Engineering
Description: Explore engineering careers in computer modelling, virtual reality environments, 3D printing and world-leading rapid prototyping capabilities. Learn how studying at Deakin will ensure you gain the practical experience and the knowledge and skills employers are looking for.

Title: Australia's water security - how can environmental engineers help?
Description: Water is a sensitive issue in Australia. How do we balance the competing demands of industry, agriculture and a growing population with the effects of climate change to provide a clean and secure water supply? Join our panel members as they discuss the role of environmental engineers in managing and protecting Australia's water resources.

Title: Engineering student Q&A panel
Description: Have a question about engineering you'd rather ask a current student? Come along to our student-led Q&A panel.

Title: Engineering
Description: Explore engineering careers in computer modelling, virtual reality environments, 3D printing and world-leading rapid prototyping capabilities. Learn how studying at Deakin will ensure you gain the practical experience and the knowledge and skills employers are looking for.

Title: Crime scene house
Description: Explore our real-life crime scene house, staged with gruesome elements forensic investigators are confronted with, including body fluids and blood, fingerprints, fibres and weapons.
Location: Departing from the Science booth, Career and Course Information Centre

Title: Mind Racer
Description: Step into the Mind Racer arena for the ultimate test of brainpower. Battle your friends and future classmates in a race of mind over matter utilising the latest in brain-computer interface technology. Do you have what it takes to land first place? There's only one way to find out.
Pre_selected: Bachelor of Information Technology; Bachelor of Health Sciences; Bachelor of Cyber Security; Bachelor of Arts

Interest_area: Humanities, social sciences and languages; Media, communication and creative arts; Education and teaching
Title: Imaginarium - learning in 360 degrees
Description: Experience a taster of Deakin's new Imaginarium - a purpose-built 360-degree immersive learning space. See how our Arts and Education students will be transported to another time and place to learn, engage and research through visual and audio simulations of endless environments, conditions and eras.

Title: Deakin residences tours
Description: Join in on one of our residence tours and discover the different types of accommodation available at our Waurn Ponds campus. Learn from the experts just what it's like to live near campus and how you can become part of our close-knit resident community.

Title: Marine research vessel
Description: Explore our research vessel and gain an insight into our unique marine habitats.

Title: Campus tours
Description: Join one of our tours to discover more of the Waurn Ponds campus. Led by our Student Ambassadors who know all the ins and outs of Deakin, you'll get a feel for campus life while learning more about our study areas, state-of-the-art facilities, and how to make the best transition into university.
Pre_selected: Bachelor of Health Sciences; Bachelor of Cyber Security; Bachelor of Arts

Title: Medical imaging lab tour
Description: Visit our state-of-the-art medical imaging labs and get a hands-on experience of the x-ray process. See students and academic staff demonstrate x-raying specialised 'phantom' manikins and find out everything you need to know about our course and the equipment our students use.

Title: Medicine lab tour
Description: Visit our medicine clinical teaching spaces to see our state-of-the-art teaching tools, including vein detection devices, human skeletons, teaching manikins and human specimens. While you're there, explore our world-class anatomy museum and see preservations of every part of the human body.

Title: Optometry practice and clinical skills lab tour
Description: Visit our working optometry practice and practical lab spaces to see how our students get real-world experience. Have a photo of your eye taken with our 3D simulation machine and take a look into the inner workings of human sight.

Title: Exercise and sport science lab tour
Description: Tour our Elite Sports Precinct which features an eight lane running track with built-in force plates, FIFA-grade soccer pitch, MCG-sized AFL oval, purpose-built teaching hub and more. Visualise how we use oxygen and the effects that strenuous physical exercise can have with our VO2 max demonstration in our physiology labs and put your reaction speed to the test in our 3D Gait timing reaction drill.

Title: Win with Deakin
Description: Enter your details to receive updates on exciting Deakin news, events and courses. Just for registering, you can spin to win instant prizes, including Deakin hoodies, beanies, bags and lollies. Find us on campus for your opportunity to walk away a winner!
Pre_selected: Bachelor of Information Technology; Bachelor of Health Sciences; Bachelor of Cyber Security; Bachelor of Arts

Title: Challenge yourself on the Deakin Reactor
Description: How do you think your hand-eye coordination compares to elite athletes? Check out our Deakin Reactor and test your skills against professional athletes from the Geelong Cats, the Melbourne Vixens and the Deakin Melbourne Boomers.

Title: Institute for Frontier Materials display
Description: At the forefront of innovation in materials design and engineering research, the Institute for Frontier Materials is the place to come for innovative research in materials science. Visit our marquee to see our latest projects.

Title: FLAIM Trainer
Description: Discover FLAIM Trainer, the ultimate virtual reality firefighting simulator. Immerse yourself in real-world scenarios through the power of virtual reality and experience for yourself the ground-breaking technology developed by Deakin's Institute for Intelligent Systems Research and Innovation (IISRI) and manufactured by FLAIM Systems Pty Ltd.
